{"parse":{"title":"Raphael Perez","pageid":57731121,"revid":850625677,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><div role=\"note\" class=\"hatnote navigation-not-searchable\">For the former IDF Chief Rabbi, see <a href=\"/wiki/Rafi_Peretz\" title=\"Rafi Peretz\">Rafi Peretz</a>.</div>\n<table class=\"infobox biography vcard\" style=\"width:22em\"><tbody><tr><th colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center;font-size:125%;font-weight:bold\"><span class=\"fn\">Raphael Perez</span></th></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center\">\n<a href=\"/wiki/File:Rafi_perez.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"Rafi perez.jpg\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/88/Rafi_perez.jpg/220px-Rafi_perez.jpg\" width=\"220\" height=\"294\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/8/88/Rafi_perez.jpg 1.5x\" data-file-width=\"318\" data-file-height=\"425\" /></a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Native&#160;name</th><td>\n<span class=\"nickname\">\u05e8\u05e4\u05d0\u05dc \u05e4\u05e8\u05e5</span></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Born</th><td>\n1965 (age&#160;52&#8211;53)<br /><span class=\"birthplace\">Jerusalem, Israel</span></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Known&#160;for</th><td>\n<a href=\"/wiki/Naive_Art\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Naive Art\">Naive Art</a></td></tr></tbody></table>\n<p><b>Raphael \"Rafi\" Perez</b> (<a href=\"/wiki/Hebrew_language\" title=\"Hebrew language\">Hebrew</a>: <span lang=\"he\" dir=\"rtl\">\u05e8\u05e4\u05d9 \u05e4\u05e8\u05e5</span>&#8206;; born 1965) is an <a href=\"/wiki/Israel\" title=\"Israel\">Israeli</a> artist known for his <a href=\"/wiki/Homoeroticism\" title=\"Homoeroticism\">homoerotic</a> gay art and colorful urban landscapes painted in a <a href=\"/wiki/Na%C3%AFve_art\" title=\"Na\u00efve art\">na\u00efve style</a>.\n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><input type=\"checkbox\" role=\"button\" id=\"toctogglecheckbox\" class=\"toctogglecheckbox\" style=\"display:none\" /><div class=\"toctitle\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><h2>Contents</h2><span class=\"toctogglespan\"><label class=\"toctogglelabel\" for=\"toctogglecheckbox\"></label></span></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#Early_life\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Early life</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#Art_career\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Art career</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#Selected_solo_exhibitions\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Selected solo exhibitions</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#Selected_group_exhibitions\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Selected group exhibitions</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-5\"><a href=\"#Permanent_exhibits\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">5</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Permanent exhibits</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-6\"><a href=\"#See_also\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">6</span> <span class=\"toctext\">See also</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-7\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">7</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Early_life\">Early life</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Raphael_Perez&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: Early life\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>Perez was born in <a href=\"/wiki/Jerusalem\" title=\"Jerusalem\">Jerusalem</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> Growing up, he was exposed to the works of great painters by his father. He has two brothers, one an industrial designer (his twin)  and the other a jewelry designer. He served in the <a href=\"/wiki/Israel_Defense_Forces\" title=\"Israel Defense Forces\">Israel Defense Forces</a> in the Artillery Corps. Perez only began to paint at the age of 23.<sup id=\"cite_ref-israel21c_2-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-israel21c-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> In 1989\u20131992, he studied art at the College of Visual Arts in <a href=\"/wiki/Beersheba\" title=\"Beersheba\">Beersheba</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup> Since 1995, he has been working and living in <a href=\"/wiki/Tel_Aviv\" title=\"Tel Aviv\">Tel Aviv</a>.<sup class=\"noprint Inline-Template Template-Fact\" style=\"white-space:nowrap;\">&#91;<i><a href=\"/wiki/Wikipedia:Citation_needed\" title=\"Wikipedia:Citation needed\"><span title=\"This claim needs references to reliable sources. (June 2018)\">citation needed</span></a></i>&#93;</sup>\n</p><p>For 15 years, Perez worked as a counselor at a youth shelter and a preschool sports and art teacher.<sup id=\"cite_ref-israel21c_2-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-israel21c-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Art_career\">Art career</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Raphael_Perez&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: Art career\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:222px;\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Raphael_Perez_Artist.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/b/b0/Raphael_Perez_Artist.jpg/220px-Raphael_Perez_Artist.jpg\" width=\"220\" height=\"136\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/b/b0/Raphael_Perez_Artist.jpg/330px-Raphael_Perez_Artist.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/b/b0/Raphael_Perez_Artist.jpg/440px-Raphael_Perez_Artist.jpg 2x\" data-file-width=\"1200\" data-file-height=\"742\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Raphael_Perez_Artist.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>Balloons over Tel Aviv</div></div></div>\n<div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:222px;\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Balcony_of_love.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"Balcony of love.jpg\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/d/db/Balcony_of_love.jpg/220px-Balcony_of_love.jpg\" width=\"220\" height=\"218\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/d/db/Balcony_of_love.jpg/330px-Balcony_of_love.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/d/db/Balcony_of_love.jpg/440px-Balcony_of_love.jpg 2x\" data-file-width=\"600\" data-file-height=\"594\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Balcony_of_love.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div></div></div></div>\n<div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:222px;\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Rotshild.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/d/df/Rotshild.jpg/220px-Rotshild.jpg\" width=\"220\" height=\"97\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/d/df/Rotshild.jpg/330px-Rotshild.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/d/df/Rotshild.jpg/440px-Rotshild.jpg 2x\" data-file-width=\"780\" data-file-height=\"343\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Rotshild.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div><a href=\"/wiki/Rothschild_Boulevard\" title=\"Rothschild Boulevard\">Rothschild Boulevard</a></div></div></div>\n<p>Perez paints urban landscapes in a na\u00efve style, depicting life in the city streets, parks and public places in a palette of  bright colors. Many of his works are grouped by series \u2013 men and women, gay families, spherical paintings of Tel Aviv and Jerusalem as multicultural centers.<sup id=\"cite_ref-israel21c_2-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-israel21c-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> His early work focused on human relationships, sometimes using flowers as a metaphor. \nPerez's artistic career began when he was still living with women. He often painted heterosexual couples, but even then one discerned Perez's inner conflicts and attempt to grapple with the complexities of couplehood.<sup id=\"cite_ref-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>In 2010, Perez was commissioned to create advertising posters for the <a href=\"/wiki/Israel_Ministry_of_Tourism\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Israel Ministry of Tourism\">Israel Ministry of Tourism</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-5\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup> His posters of Tel Aviv appeared on billboards in the London underground, shopping malls and bus stops, and his designs were featured on 30,000 transportation card holders distributed in London. He describes his art as \"a reflection of the entire gay community \u2013 people in the closet, mature love, gay families, gay political icons and cultural icons\".<sup id=\"cite_ref-israel21c_2-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-israel21c-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> Major influences on his work are <a href=\"/wiki/Nahum_Gutman\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Nahum Gutman\">Nahum Gutman</a> and <a href=\"/wiki/David_Hockney\" title=\"David Hockney\">David Hockney</a>. \n</p><p>Perez's work was described in <a href=\"/wiki/The_London_Magazine\" title=\"The London Magazine\">The London Magazine</a> as \"instantly appealing, bursting with exuberance and energy\".<sup id=\"cite_ref-6\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup> According to the <a href=\"/wiki/Jerusalem_Post\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Jerusalem Post\">Jerusalem Post</a>, Perez is a \"Tel Aviv artist in every sense of the word \u2013 painting the urban landscape of the city\u2026 infused with happiness.\"<sup id=\"cite_ref-7\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-7\">&#91;7&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Selected_solo_exhibitions\">Selected solo exhibitions</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Raphael_Perez&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" title=\"Edit section: Selected solo exhibitions\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li>The Kiss, Zaritsky Artists House, Tel Aviv \u2013 December 18, 2008<sup id=\"cite_ref-imj_8-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-imj-8\">&#91;8&#93;</a></sup></li>\n<li>Army of lovers, <a href=\"/wiki/Janco_Dada_Museum\" title=\"Janco Dada Museum\">Janco Dada Museum</a>, Ein Hod \u2013 2009<sup id=\"cite_ref-imj_8-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-imj-8\">&#91;8&#93;</a></sup></li>\n<li>Zaritsky Artists House, Tel Aviv \u2013 2008</li>\n<li>Zaritsky Artists House, Tel Aviv \u2013 2006</li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Selected_group_exhibitions\">Selected group exhibitions</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Raphael_Perez&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" title=\"Edit section: Selected group exhibitions\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li>Art Workshop Gallery, Yavne \u2013 2017</li>\n<li>Minus One Galley \u2013 2017</li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Umm_al-Fahm_Art_Gallery\" title=\"Umm al-Fahm Art Gallery\">Umm al-Fahm Art Gallery</a> \u2013 2014</li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Sommer_Contemporary_Art\" title=\"Sommer Contemporary Art\">Sommer Contemporary Art</a> \u2013 2010</li>\n<li>Office Gallery \u2013 2008</li>\n<li>Joseph Weisman Municipal Art Gallery, Givatayim \u2013 2008</li>\n<li>Zaritsky Artists House, Tel Aviv \u2013 2007</li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Tel_Aviv_Museum_of_Art\" title=\"Tel Aviv Museum of Art\">Tel Aviv Museum of Art</a> \u2013 2003</li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Permanent_exhibits\">Permanent exhibits</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Raphael_Perez&amp;action=edit&amp;section=5\" title=\"Edit section: Permanent exhibits\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li>Since 2018 at The Chaim Rosenberg School of Jewish Studies (<a href=\"/wiki/Tel_Aviv_University\" title=\"Tel Aviv University\">Tel Aviv University</a>)</li>\n<li>Since 2016 at The <a href=\"/wiki/International_Convention_Center_(Jerusalem)\" title=\"International Convention Center (Jerusalem)\">International Convention Center (Jerusalem)</a></li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"See_also\">See also</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Raphael_Perez&amp;action=edit&amp;section=6\" title=\"Edit section: See also\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li><a href=\"/wiki/Visual_arts_in_Israel\" title=\"Visual arts in Israel\">Visual arts in Israel</a></li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Raphael_Perez&amp;action=edit&amp;section=7\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"reflist\" style=\"list-style-type: decimal;\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-1\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://artmarketmag.com/raphael-perez/\">ArtMarket magazine</a></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-israel21c-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">^ <a href=\"#cite_ref-israel21c_2-0\"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href=\"#cite_ref-israel21c_2-1\"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a> <a href=\"#cite_ref-israel21c_2-2\"><sup><i><b>c</b></i></sup></a> <a href=\"#cite_ref-israel21c_2-3\"><sup><i><b>d</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.israel21c.org/the-gay-painter-of-tel-aviv/\">The gay painter of Tel Aviv</a></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-3\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-3\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.saatchiart.com/Raphael\">Saatchi Art: Raphael Perez</a></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-4\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-4\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.artworks.co.il/?p=2280\">Rafi Perez (1965)</a></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-5\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-5\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://embassies.gov.il/hong-kong/AboutIsrael/AboutIsraelInfo/Pages/Tel-Aviv-through-a-gay-painter%E2%80%99s-eyes.aspx\">Tel Aviv through a gay painter</a></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-6\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-6\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.thelondonmagazine.co.uk\">Freedom of Expression: True Colours</a></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-7\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-7\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.jpost.com/Israel-News/Culture/Israeli-art-Upgrading-our-presence-of-mind-462547\">Israeli art: Upgrading our presence  of mind, </a><a href=\"/wiki/Jerusalem_Post\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Jerusalem Post\">Jerusalem Post</a></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-imj-8\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">^ <a href=\"#cite_ref-imj_8-0\"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href=\"#cite_ref-imj_8-1\"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://museum.imj.org.il/artcenter/newsite/en/exhibitions/?artist=Perez,%20Raphael&amp;list=P\">Information Center or Israeli Art, Israel Museum</a></span>\n</li>\n</ol></div></div>\n\n<!-- \nNewPP limit report\nParsed by mw2211\nCached time: 20180921120446\nCache expiry: 86400\nDynamic content: true\nCPU time usage: 0.336 seconds\nReal time usage: 0.408 seconds\nPreprocessor visited node count: 1371/1000000\nPreprocessor generated node count: 0/1500000\nPost\u2010expand include size: 6362/2097152 bytes\nTemplate argument size: 1248/2097152 bytes\nHighest expansion depth: 14/40\nExpensive parser function count: 1/500\nUnstrip recursion depth: 0/20\nUnstrip post\u2010expand size: 3768/5000000 bytes\nNumber of Wikibase entities loaded: 1/400\nLua time usage: 0.191/10.000 seconds\nLua memory usage: 9.51 MB/50 MB\n-->\n<!--\nTransclusion expansion time report (%,ms,calls,template)\n100.00%  364.347      1 -total\n 36.36%  132.468      1 Template:Lang-he\n 31.11%  113.331      1 Template:Infobox_artist\n 29.33%  106.862      1 Template:Infobox_person\n 19.19%   69.913      1 Template:Infobox\n 11.82%   43.059      1 Template:Cn\n 10.07%   36.672      1 Template:Fix\n  7.66%   27.894      1 Template:For\n  6.42%   23.394      1 Template:Authority_control\n  6.22%   22.646      2 Template:Category_handler\n-->\n\n<!-- Saved in parser cache with key enwiki:pcache:idhash:57731121-0!canonical and timestamp 20180921120446 and revision id 850625677\n -->\n</div>"},"langlinks":[{"lang":"he","url":"https://he.wikipedia.org/wiki/%D7%A8%D7%A4%D7%99_%D7%A4%D7%A8%D7%A5_(%D7%A6%D7%99%D7%99%D7%A8)","langname":"Hebrew","autonym":"\u05e2\u05d1\u05e8\u05d9\u05ea","*":"\u05e8\u05e4\u05d9 \u05e4\u05e8\u